description.en:
Concordium is the Layer-1 blockchain built for a new era of digital trust. With mandatory, privacy-preserving identity verification built into its consensus layer, utilizing zero-knowledge proof technology. Concordium also enables Protocol-level tokens that eliminate smart contract risks by being issued directly at the consensus layer, with built-in features that provide the infrastructure for compliance-ready use cases.
At its core is Smart Money - programmable, identity-embedded, and compliance-ready value that powers trusted interactions across Web3. Smart Money enables frictionless exchange, automation, and verifiable trust by design. Unlike conventional blockchains, Concordium integrates trust, accountability, and privacy into its architecture from the ground up  bridging traditional systems and Web3 to build a transparent, sustainable digital future.
The name Concordium comes from the Latin concordia—meaning harmony and agreement—a reflection of its mission to build infrastructure that embeds trust, privacy, and compliance into every interaction.
